text_en:
Indulge with a new way of appreciating arts with the Immersive Multi-Sensory Experience that brings together the masterpieces by &amp;ldquo;Claude Monet&amp;rdquo;, a French artist known to be one of the most influential icons of the world and one of the pioneers of the Impressionism movement in the 19th century. &amp;nbsp;Monet had created countless stunning paintings that artistically portray the ambience of nature and landscapes using colors to capture the visionary seen though his eyes rather than using lines and shapes &amp;ndash; a conventional method and elements use by past artists. &amp;nbsp;His work is showcased along with 14 other Impressionist artists for visitors to immerse themselves in the unique experience.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
A collection of over 3,500 masterpieces by the selected artists are presented through a cutting-edge technology on massive screens, using over 58 projectors within a space of more than 4,000 m2 in size and projecting pieces from famous artists including Claude Monet, Henri de Toulouse-Lautrec, Georges Seurat, &amp;Eacute;douard Manet, Paul C&amp;eacute;zanne, Paul Signac, Camille Pissarro, Gustave Courbet, Henri-Edmond Cross, Pierre-Auguste Renoir, Berthe Morisot, Armand Guillaumin, Edgar Degas, Mary Cassatt, and Alfred Sisley&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Ticket prices are at THB 990 and THB 1,490 for VIP tickets.&lt;br /&gt;
Purchase you tickets at &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.liveimpact-event.com/th/home/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;https://www.liveimpact-event.com/th/home/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Exhibition starts from 22nd Sep 2023 to 14th Feb 2024&lt;br /&gt;
Venue: Attraction Hall, 6th Floor of ICONSIAM&lt;br /&gt;
Opening times: 10.30 - 21.00&lt;br /&gt;
